headline: Qualcomm Is Going After Intel and AMD in This Lucrative Market
summary: The server CPU market has long been dominated by Intel (NASDAQ: INTC) and AMD (NASDAQ: AMD).  Both companies make chips based on the x86 architecture.  While there are other types of CPUs used for specialized purposes -- think IBM mainframes -- x86 reigns supreme in the data center.
